liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Morocco have their first ever World Cup win! After going down 6-0 to Germany in their first game, Morocco have now given themselves a chance of making it through to the knockout rounds, with three points against South Korea. The 6th minute goal from Jraidi was enough in an evenly contested game. South Korea toiled but seemed to lack ideas on how to break the Moroccans down, and the scoreline could have been bigger had the African side taken their chances. Bernadette Clarke at the ground: "They were desperate for a win and vocal about exactly that. The smiles on their faces say it all."
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: FULL-TIME: South Korea 0 - 1 Morocco

children.content: Morocco have their first ever World Cup win!
After going down 6-0 to Germany in their first game, Morocco have now given themselves a chance of making it through to the knockout rounds, with three points against South Korea.
The 6th minute goal from Jraidi was enough in an evenly contested game.
South Korea toiled but seemed to lack ideas on how to break the Moroccans down, and the scoreline could have been bigger had the African side taken their chances.
Bernadette Clarke at the ground: "They were desperate for a win and vocal about exactly that. The smiles on their faces say it all."

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: A minor upset on the cards here, in what has been a close game. Jraidi's angled header was the difference. It's been an interesting contrast in styles, with Korea trying for some patient build-up before targetting their tall players in the middle, while Morocco have been playing some nice passing football when they break in attack. They need to be a bit more potent in front of goal though.
